The two brothers are fighting for one of Victoria's largest real estate empires worth more than $500 million - forty years after their Italian ancestors founded the dynasty.
Former Carleton Football Club director and developer Colin de Lütis lives in Turac Palace through three doors from his younger brother Paul, who filed a lawsuit against him in the Supreme Court for the division of possessions and assets.
