However, the court released her from responsibility in connection with reconciliation with the injured father.
The prosecution believes that the crime should not be left unpunished, so as not to create a precedent for other HIV dissidents.
The case against a resident of Tyumen was initiated under part 1 of Article 109 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (cause of death by negligence) in April - after her three-year-old daughter died of HIV infection in the 4th stage.
According to the prosecutor’s office, the mother herself is HIV-infected.
