The prosecutor's office disagreed with the court's decision and appealed, demanding that the decision to terminate the case be annulled and sent to a new hearing.
The girl died, and it is impossible to compensate for the damage caused by the crime.
The HIV-infected mother, contrary to the recommendations of doctors, refused to examine the baby and treat her for a dangerous infection," the press service of the prosecutor's office said.
According to the supervisory authority, it should be punished, otherwise it will be followed by other HIV dissidents.
As told in the Tyumen AIDS Center, now in the Tyumen region about 12 children with HIV do not receive medical care due to the refusal of parents.
"And this situation has already improved - during the year of the work of the special group, half of the parents who categorically refused to treat children with HIV, changed their opinion - allowed to conduct a diagnosis, began to take drugs," said Elena Loseva, a spokesman for the AIDS Center.
According to her, it is impossible to influence parents in a legislative way, and as a result, not all HIV-infected children can be detected - mothers do not allow them to be examined, hide, run away with children from hospitals.
What are the dangers of HIV-dissidents
At the end of last year, St. Petersburg sociologists presented the results of Russia’s first study of the so-called HIV dissident movement.
HIV dissidents are people who deny the existence of HIV and refuse to take medication.
Doctors and activists of AIDS service NGOs call such views anti-medical, and see their spread as a serious threat.
