Drug trafficking in Sinaloa is “a way of life,” he said last October in an interview with Rompeviento TV.
“You have to accept the tasks that fall on you as a journalist – either that or you’re just a fool.”
I don't want to be asked, "What did you do when there were so many deaths around... why didn't you tell me what was going on?"
The Riodos staff miss Valdez, a prankster who scoffed like a porter, a friend generous with hugs and advice, a teacher who knew how to stay alive.
They depended on their order.
