In the room where Riodose employees gathered for security training, it was suddenly forbidden to bring cell phones: a few days before it became known that spy programs, which are sold exclusively to governments, are used in Mexico to monitor journalists and public activists.
Outside, two policemen hide in the shade of a tree from 104 degrees Celsius (40 degrees Celsius).
