The experimentation and improvisation of jazzmen is valued as highly as scientists.
One of the main events of the festival will be the performance of Azekel, a British man of Nigerian origin, known as his own work, as well as joint work with the legendary Massive Attack and Gorillaz.
Jazz lovers are looking forward to the first performance in Russia of the five-time Grammy Award nominee, pianist Christian Sands (USA) with his trio.
In the new capacity will try one of the best academic chamber orchestras "Music Viva" under the leadership of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of pianist Yuri Favorin.
The fusion of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions will be demonstrated by the Marimba Plus ensemble and its leader, composer and performer Lea Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to become the set of the prize winner Sergey Kurehin Anton Maskeliadze.
An experimental artist controls music and video with gestures – that’s how Leap Motion technology works.
In total, eight musical groups will perform on two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive zones and art objects, combined with the idea of merging music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit a scientific buffet and observe the creation of cryo-ice cream or rocky sands from starch and water.
In the special zone of vinyl it will be possible to buy records of current jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including music, popular science and biomedical literature.
