Electricity is cheaper for residents and for commodity producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (East Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers are beginning to bear fruit.
Since September 1, the cost of low-voltage electricity for industrial recipients has been reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Market of Electricity and Power and to the Consolidated Forecast Balance of Electricity Production and Supply (Power) within the framework of the Unified Energy System of the Republic of Russia for the Subjects of the Russian Federation" (from 17.07.2017 No 842) established indicative prices for electricity and power
As a result, the cost of electricity for Buryat producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate life for small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the republic’s leaders have been beating the thresholds of Moscow’s cabinets in vain attempts to level the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with the cascade of hydroelectric power plants on Angara flowing from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
It was only this year that the movement began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles / kWh to 3.93 rubles / kWh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of wholesale price zones, for which the peculiarities of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, a number of industrial consumers have emerged.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays for a kilowatt-hour of 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of the new tariff moves towards a downward trend for Buryatia.
