The National Union of Unskilled, Municipal and Boiler Workers (GMB) is concerned about the investment at McVitie’s factory in Glasgow.
The union requires assurances from the managers of the biscuit maker McVitie’s in connection with its long-term commitment to manufacture at the Glasgow plant.
The Scottish branch of GMB reports that the company has been silent about the issue of future investments at the Tolcross facility.
The factory, which produces, among other products, Hobnobs cookies and Rich Tea, employs more than 500 people.
