When Manchester City expressed interest in hiring Blaise Matuidi in 2014, Nasser Al-Helaifi issued a strong warning to any club that wanted to lure one of PSG’s best players.
“I don’t worry because they know that if they touch one of our players, then we will stand against them, we will make offers to their players,” he said.
