In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaz" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where 15,000 people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment in the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will operate in the TOR "Abaz" includes, for example, crop production, animal husbandry, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed a framework agreement on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of Abakan Mine LLC.
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of TOPs.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, an area of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will allow to diversify the economy of the monocity, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of Ural Steel JSC, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOP will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the mono-towns of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOR.
The territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment to improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of TOR can be identified the following: a profit tax of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rental rates.
